---------------kubectl commands------------------

minikube start <cluster_name>

1. display the cluster info
   kubectl cluster-info

2. display cluster nodes
   kubectl get nodes

3. dosplay all info about nodes
   kubectl describe nodes

4. to display any one node info
   kubectl describe nodes <node_name>

5. create the deployment in the cluster
   kubectl create deployment <name> --image=<image_name>

6. show the deployment
   kubectl get deployment

7. scale the deployment / create the replicas in the deployment
   kubectl scale deployment <deployment_name> --replicas=3
	 #it will create the pods/container in the cluster

8. to see the IP of pods
   kubectl get pods -o wide

9. to see the graphical interface
   minikube dashboard

10. to delete all clusters 
    minikube delete

11.  
